ity_path=path)\\n+sdp/logs/Verify_T-019_20260416T043834Z_1776324455.log:13652:sdp/logs/Verify_T-008_20260408T223256Z_1775692000.log:1693:tests/test_first_boot.py:470:        identity = bootstrap_identity(\\n+sdp/logs/Verify_T-019_20260416T043834Z_1776324455.log:13653:sdp/logs/Verify_T-008_20260408T223256Z_1775692000.log:1716:my-claw/tools/first_boot.py:224:def bootstrap_identity(\\n+sdp/logs/Verify_T-019_20260416T043834Z_1776324455.log:13654:sdp/logs/Verify_T-008_20260408T223256Z_1775692000.log:2055:/bin/zsh -lc \\\"cd /Users/anthony/Programming/PromptClaw && rg -n \\\\\\\"FirstBootAnnouncer|identity\\\\\\\\.json|bootstrap_identity|mint_identity|identity_path|announced\\\\\\\" my-claw/tools/preflight.py my-claw/tools/daemon.py my-claw/tools/cypherclaw_daemon.py my-claw/tools/init_workdir.sh\\\" in /Users/anthony/Programming/PromptClaw\\n+sdp/logs/Verify_T-019_20260416T043834Z_1776324455.log:13655:sdp/logs/Verify_T-008_20260408T223256Z_1775692000.log:2156:\\\"'`bootstrap_identity` and `generate_artistic_name` are correctly implemented and write an identity record using UUIDs and randomized adjective-noun names. The code includes persistence and idempotent load behavior. However, the runtime startup path does not invoke identity bootstrap, so the “first boot generates” behavior is not proven in the actual boot flow.\\n+sdp/logs/Verify_T-019_20260416T043834Z_1776324455.log:13656:sdp/logs/Verify_T-008_20260408T223256Z_1775692000.log:2159:The implementation has unit coverage for `bootstrap_identity` and name generation, including corrupt-file and persistence cases. Integration coverage is missing: there is no call site that runs bootstrap during system startup.\\n+sdp/logs/Verify_T-019_20260416T043834Z_1776324455.log:13657:sdp/logs/Verify_T-008_20260408T223256Z_1775692000.log:2171:- [ ] Runtime does not call `bootstrap_identity` on startup, so identity files are not guaranteed to be created automatically on first boot (for example, startup loop creates `FirstBootAnnouncer` and then only reads identity for announcement). Severity: blocking\\n+sdp/logs/Verify_T-019_20260416T043834Z_1776324455.log:13658:sdp/logs/Verify_T-008_20260408T223256Z_1775692000.log:2176:- Wire `bootstrap_identity()` into the first-boot execution path before first-boot announcement logic (e.g., in daemon startup) and persist the returned identity.\\n+sdp/logs/Verify_T-019_20260416T043834Z_1776324455.log:13659:sdp/logs/Verify_T-008_20260408T223256Z_1775692000.log:2255:\\\"'`bootstrap_identity` and `generate_artistic_name` are implemented correctly and include UUID instance IDs, adjective-noun names, persistence, and load-once logic. Runtime usage is not fully wired: startup code currently only attempts to load identity for announcement and does not bootstrap when missing, so identity creation on first boot is not guaranteed.\\n+sdp/logs/Verify_T-019_20260416T043834Z_1776324455.log:13660:sdp/logs/Verify_T-008_20260408T223256Z_1775692000.log:2270:- [ ] Runtime does not invoke `bootstrap_identity` on startup, so the identity file is never guaranteed to be created automatically at first run. Severity: blocking\\n+sdp/logs/Verify_T-019_20260416T043834Z_1776324455.log:13661:sdp/logs/Verify_T-008_20260408T223256Z_1775692000.log:2275:- Add `bootstrap_identity()` invocation in startup flow (before `FirstBootAnnouncer`) so first boots mint and persist identity automatically.\\n+sdp/logs/Verify_T-019_20260416T043834Z_1776324455.log:13662:sdp/logs/Verify_T-008_20260408T223256Z_1775692000.log:2290:\\\"'`bootstrap_identity` and `generate_artistic_name` are implemented correctly and include UUID instance IDs, adjective-noun names, persistence, and load-once logic. Runtime usage is not fully wired: startup code currently only attempts to load identity for announcement and does not bootstrap when missing, so identity creation on first boot is not guaranteed.\\n+sdp/logs/Verify_T-019_20260416T043834Z_1776324455.log:13663:sdp/logs/Verify_T-008_20260408T223256Z_1775692000.log:2305: